    "description":  "A statutory demand is a formal written demand for payment of a debt within 21 days.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eHelp us to improve the director information hub by \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.smartsurvey.co.uk/s/28AKK8/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003ecompleting a short feedback survey.\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen a company owes money to a creditor, the creditor can make a statutory demand for payment of the debt. Statutory demands can also be made against individuals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"making-a-statutory-demandto-a-company\"\u003eMaking a statutory demand to a company\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen you make a \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/statutory-demands\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003estatutory demand\u003c/a\u003e, or someone makes one against your company, the company has 21 days to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003epay the debt \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ereach an agreement to pay \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf there is no response after 21 days and the debt is over £750, an application can be made \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/wind-up-a-company-that-owes-you-money\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eto wind the company up\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"failure-to-respond\"\u003eFailure to respond\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFailure to respond to a statutory demand can have consequences for any company that wishes to continue trading. If you do not deal with a statutory demand you risk:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ea winding-up petition being issued against the company\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ecredit being affected when others become aware of the demand\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou should consider seeking legal advice if you receive a statutory demand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"challenging-statutory-demands\"\u003eChallenging statutory demands \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou cannot challenge a statutory demand made against companies.  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA company can apply to court to stop creditors from applying to wind the company up. However, this has to be done within 21 days of getting the statutory demand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eRead more about \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/protecting-company-from-compulsory-liquidation/statutory-demand\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eresponding to a statutory demand\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/director-information-hub\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGo back to the director information hub homepage\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
